# Timeline Page Design Pattern

## Template Structure

### Required Imports and Variables
```nunjucks
{% extends "layouts/forms.html" %}
{% from "moj/components/timeline/macro.njk" import mojTimeline %}
{% from "govuk/components/select/macro.njk" import govukSelect %}
{% from "govuk/components/details/macro.njk" import govukDetails %}
{% set signedIn = 'true' %}
{% set fullWidth = true %}
{% set hideButton = true %}
{% set breadcrumb = true %}
{% set showSubheader = true %}
{% set subHeader = 'Showing result for' %}
{% set title = 'MRN_CODE_HERE' %}
{% set bodyClasses = 'mrn accordion v4' %}
{% set cssClassName = 'timeline' %}
{% set hideManageAccount = 'false' %}
{% set showEdit = true %}
{% set hideBackLink = true %}
{% set showMenu = true %}
{% set searchLinkHref = '../search' %}
{% set menu = true %}
```

### Tab Structure
- Two tabs: "Latest" (summary view) and "Timeline" (timeline view)
- Timeline tab should be selected by default: `govuk-tabs__list-item--selected`
- Latest tab contains MRN containers and CHED sections
- Timeline tab contains JavaScript data and timeline container

## Timeline Data Structure

### JavaScript Data Format
```javascript
<script>
  window.timelineData = [
    {
      title: 'Event Title - Subheader',  // Split by " - " for main title and subheader
      version: 2,                        // Optional: version number (not shown for BTMS decision)
      cdsStatus: 'Finalised - Released', // Optional: CDS status (shows as colored tag)
      chedStatus: 'Valid',               // Optional: CHED status (shows as colored tag)
      decision: '6',                     // Optional: Decision (shows as "Version" for BTMS decision, "Decision" otherwise)
      created: '2025-11-06T09:24:20Z',  // Required: ISO timestamp (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ)
      hasDetails: true,                  // Boolean: whether to show expandable details
      detailsHtml: `                     // Required if hasDetails: true - HTML string
        <h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-0">Item 1 - Name</h3>
        <p class="commodity-code"><strong>Commodity code:</strong> 1234567890</p>
        <table class="govuk-table">
          <!-- Table structure -->
        </table>
      `
    }
  ];
</script>
```

### Timeline Tab Structure
```nunjucks
<!-- TIMELINE TAB -->
<div class="govuk-tabs__panel" id="timeline">
  <script>
    window.timelineData = [ /* array of events */ ];
  </script>
  
  {% include 'includes/timeline-filters.html' %}
  
  <div id="timeline-container">
    <!-- Timeline will be rendered here by JavaScript -->
  </div>
</div>
```

## Details HTML Structure

When `hasDetails: true`, the `detailsHtml` must contain:

### Item Headings
- First item: `<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-0">Item X - Name</h3>`
- Subsequent items: `<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-4">` or `<h3 class="govuk-heading-s govuk-!-margin-top-4">`

### Commodity Code
```html
<p class="commodity-code"><strong>Commodity code:</strong> CODE</p>
```

### Table Columns
- Always include: CHED reference, Check code, Authority
- Sometimes include: Decision code, Decision (for BTMS decision events)
- Use GOV.UK table structure with proper `<thead>` and `<tbody>`

### Example Details HTML
```html
<h3 class="govuk-heading-m govuk-!-margin-top-0">Item 1 - Sweet pepper</h3>
<p class="commodity-code"><strong>Commodity code:</strong> 1601009999</p>
<table class="govuk-table">
  <thead class="govuk-table__head">
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">CHED reference</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Check code</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Authority</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Decision code</th>
      <th scope="col" class="govuk-table__header">Decision</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody class="govuk-table__body">
    <tr class="govuk-table__row">
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">GBCHD2025.6802963</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">H223</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">FNAO</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">C03</td>
      <td class="govuk-table__cell">Release - Inspection Complete</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```

## Event Title Patterns

- CDS events: `'CDS finalisation - CDS to BTMS'`, `'CDS decision request - CDS to BTMS'`
- BTMS events: `'BTMS decision - BTMS to CDS'`
- CHED events: `'CHEDPP GB 2025.6801816 - IPAFFS to BTMS'`, `'CHEDD.GB.2025.6803042 - IPAFFS to BTMS'`
- Error events: `'Error - Description'`, `'CDS processing error - Description'`

## Status Tag Colors

### CDS Status
- Green: `'Finalised - Released'`, `'Finalised - Manually released'`
- Red: `'Finalised - Cancelled after arrival'`
- Yellow: Contains `'In progress'` or `'Hold'`

### CHED Status
- Green: `'Valid'`
- Yellow: `'In progress'`
- Grey: `'Submitted'`

## Important Notes

1. **Dates**: Must be ISO format `'2025-11-06T09:24:20Z'` (JavaScript formats for display)
2. **Table Structure**: Always use GOV.UK table classes and proper semantic HTML
3. **Details Expandable**: Only show if `hasDetails: true` and `detailsHtml` is provided
4. **Filtering**: Timeline filters are included via `includes/timeline-filters.html`
5. **JavaScript**: Auto-initializes from `window.timelineData` on page load via `timeline.js`
6. **Decision Field**: For BTMS decision events, `decision` shows as "Version" label, otherwise shows as "Decision" label
7. **Version Field**: Not displayed for BTMS decision events (decision field is used instead)

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

- ❌ Missing `window.timelineData` assignment
- ❌ Incorrect date format (must be ISO)
- ❌ Missing `timeline-container` div
- ❌ Incorrect heading classes in detailsHtml
- ❌ Missing `timeline-filters.html` include
- ❌ Wrong table structure (missing thead/tbody)
- ❌ Forgetting to set Timeline tab as selected by default
